searchData={"content_type":"text/markdown","items":[{"doc":"AttractorPhoenix keeps the contexts that define your domain\nand business logic.\n\nContexts are also responsible for managing your data, regardless\nif it comes from the database, an external API or others.","ref":"AttractorPhoenix.html","title":"AttractorPhoenix","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.html","title":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer","type":"module"},{"doc":"Delivers an email.\n\nIf the email is delivered it returns an `{:ok, result}` tuple. If it fails,\nreturns an `{:error, error}` tuple.","ref":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.html#deliver/2","title":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.deliver/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Delivers an email, raises on error.\n\nIf the email is delivered, it returns the result. If it fails, it raises\na `DeliveryError`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.html#deliver!/2","title":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.deliver!/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Delivers a list of emails.\n\nIt accepts a list of `%Swoosh.Email{}` as its first parameter.","ref":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.html#deliver_many/2","title":"AttractorPhoenix.Mailer.deliver_many/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"The entrypoint for defining your web interface, such\nas controllers, components, channels, and so on.\n\nThis can be used in your application as:\n\n    use AttractorPhoenixWeb, :controller\n    use AttractorPhoenixWeb, :html\n\nThe definitions below will be executed for every controller,\ncomponent, etc, so keep them short and clean, focused\non imports, uses and aliases.\n\nDo NOT define functions inside the quoted expressions\nbelow. Instead, define additional modules and import\nthose modules here.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb","type":"module"},{"doc":"When used, dispatch to the appropriate controller/live_view/etc.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#__using__/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.__using__/1","type":"macro"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#channel/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.channel/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#controller/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.controller/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#html/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#live_component/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.live_component/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#live_view/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.live_view/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#router/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.router/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#static_paths/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.static_paths/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.html#verified_routes/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.verified_routes/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Provides core UI components.\n\nAt first glance, this module may seem daunting, but its goal is to provide\ncore building blocks for your application, such as tables, forms, and\ninputs. The components consist mostly of markup and are well-documented\nwith doc strings and declarative assigns. You may customize and style\nthem in any way you want, based on your application growth and needs.\n\nThe foundation for styling is Tailwind CSS, a utility-first CSS framework,\naugmented with daisyUI, a Tailwind CSS plugin that provides UI components\nand themes. Here are useful references:\n\n  * [daisyUI](https://daisyui.com/docs/intro/) - a good place to get\n    started and see the available components.\n\n  * [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com) - the foundational framework\n    we build on. You will use it for layout, sizing, flexbox, grid, and\n    spacing.\n\n  * [Heroicons](https://heroicons.com) - see `icon/1` for usage.\n\n  * [Phoenix.Component](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix_live_view/Phoenix.Component.html) -\n    the component system used by Phoenix. Some components, such as `<.link>`\n    and `<.form>`, are defined there.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents","type":"module"},{"doc":"Renders a button with navigation support.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"<.button>Send!</.button>\n    <.button phx-click=\"go\" variant=\"primary\">Send!</.button>\n    <.button navigate={~p\"/\"}>Home</.button>","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `class` (`:any`)\n* `variant` (`:string`) - Must be one of `\"primary\"`.\n* Global attributes are accepted. Supports all globals plus: `[\"href\", \"navigate\", \"patch\", \"method\", \"download\", \"name\", \"value\", \"disabled\"]`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `inner_block` (required)","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1-slots","title":"Slots - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders flash notices.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"<.flash kind={:info} flash={@flash} />\n    <.flash kind={:info} phx-mounted={show(\"#flash\")}>Welcome Back!</.flash>","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `id` (`:string`) - the optional id of flash container.\n* `flash` (`:map`) - the map of flash messages to display. Defaults to `%{}`.\n* `title` (`:string`) - Defaults to `nil`.\n* `kind` (`:atom`) - used for styling and flash lookup. Must be one of `:info`, or `:error`.\n* Global attributes are accepted. the arbitrary HTML attributes to add to the flash container.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `inner_block` - the optional inner block that renders the flash message.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1-slots","title":"Slots - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a header with title.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#header/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.header/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `inner_block` (required)\n* `subtitle`\n* `actions`","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#header/1-slots","title":"Slots - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.header/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#hide/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.hide/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a [Heroicon](https://heroicons.com).\n\nHeroicons come in three styles – outline, solid, and mini.\nBy default, the outline style is used, but solid and mini may\nbe applied by using the `-solid` and `-mini` suffix.\n\nYou can customize the size and colors of the icons by setting\nwidth, height, and background color classes.\n\nIcons are extracted from the `deps/heroicons` directory and bundled within\nyour compiled app.css by the plugin in `assets/vendor/heroicons.js`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#icon/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.icon/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"<.icon name=\"hero-x-mark\" />\n    <.icon name=\"hero-arrow-path\" class=\"ml-1 size-3 motion-safe:animate-spin\" />","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#icon/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.icon/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `name` (`:string`) (required)\n* `class` (`:any`) - Defaults to `\"size-4\"`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#icon/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.icon/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders an input with label and error messages.\n\nA `Phoenix.HTML.FormField` may be passed as argument,\nwhich is used to retrieve the input name, id, and values.\nOtherwise all attributes may be passed explicitly.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"This function accepts all HTML input types, considering that:\n\n  * You may also set `type=\"select\"` to render a ` ` tag\n\n  * `type=\"checkbox\"` is used exclusively to render boolean values\n\n  * For live file uploads, see `Phoenix.Component.live_file_input/1`\n\nSee https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input\nfor more information. Unsupported types, such as radio, are best\nwritten directly in your templates.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-types","title":"Types - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"```heex\n<.input field={@form[:email]} type=\"email\" />\n<.input name=\"my-input\" errors={[\"oh no!\"]} />\n```","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"When using `type=\"select\"`, you must pass the `options` and optionally\na `value` to mark which option should be preselected.\n\n```heex\n<.input field={@form[:user_type]} type=\"select\" options={[\"Admin\": \"admin\", \"User\": \"user\"]} />\n```\n\nFor more information on what kind of data can be passed to `options` see\n[`options_for_select`](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix_html/Phoenix.HTML.Form.html#options_for_select/2).","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-select-type","title":"Select type - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `id` (`:any`) - Defaults to `nil`.\n* `name` (`:any`)\n* `label` (`:string`) - Defaults to `nil`.\n* `value` (`:any`)\n* `type` (`:string`) - Defaults to `\"text\"`. Must be one of `\"checkbox\"`, `\"color\"`, `\"date\"`, `\"datetime-local\"`, `\"email\"`, `\"file\"`, `\"month\"`, `\"number\"`, `\"password\"`, `\"search\"`, `\"select\"`, `\"tel\"`, `\"text\"`, `\"textarea\"`, `\"time\"`, `\"url\"`, `\"week\"`, or `\"hidden\"`.\n* `field` (`Phoenix.HTML.FormField`) - a form field struct retrieved from the form, for example: @form[:email].\n* `errors` (`:list`) - Defaults to `[]`.\n* `checked` (`:boolean`) - the checked flag for checkbox inputs.\n* `prompt` (`:string`) - the prompt for select inputs. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `options` (`:list`) - the options to pass to Phoenix.HTML.Form.options_for_select/2.\n* `multiple` (`:boolean`) - the multiple flag for select inputs. Defaults to `false`.\n* `class` (`:any`) - the input class to use over defaults. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `error_class` (`:any`) - the input error class to use over defaults. Defaults to `nil`.\n* Global attributes are accepted. Supports all globals plus: `[\"accept\", \"autocomplete\", \"capture\", \"cols\", \"disabled\", \"form\", \"list\", \"max\", \"maxlength\", \"min\", \"minlength\", \"multiple\", \"pattern\", \"placeholder\", \"readonly\", \"required\", \"rows\", \"size\", \"step\"]`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a data list.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#list/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.list/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"<.list>\n      <:item title=\"Title\">{@post.title}</:item>\n      <:item title=\"Views\">{@post.views}</:item>\n    </.list>","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#list/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.list/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `item` (required) - Accepts attributes:\n\n  * `title` (`:string`) (required)","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#list/1-slots","title":"Slots - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.list/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#show/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.show/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a table with generic styling.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"<.table id=\"users\" rows={@users}>\n      <:col :let={user} label=\"id\">{user.id}</:col>\n      <:col :let={user} label=\"username\">{user.username}</:col>\n    </.table>","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `id` (`:string`) (required)\n* `rows` (`:list`) (required)\n* `row_id` (`:any`) - the function for generating the row id. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `row_click` (`:any`) - the function for handling phx-click on each row. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `row_item` (`:any`) - the function for mapping each row before calling the :col and :action slots. Defaults to `&Function.identity/1`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `col` (required) - Accepts attributes:\n\n  * `label` (`:string`)\n* `action` - the slot for showing user actions in the last table column.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1-slots","title":"Slots - AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Translates an error message using gettext.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#translate_error/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.translate_error/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Translates the errors for a field from a keyword list of errors.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.html#translate_errors/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.CoreComponents.translate_errors/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.DashboardLive.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.DashboardLive","type":"module"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.LiveView.render/1 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.DashboardLive.html#render/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.DashboardLive.render/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint","type":"module"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast/3 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast/3","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.broadcast/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast!/3 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast!/3","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.broadcast!/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast_from/4 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast_from/4","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.broadcast_from/4","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast_from!/4 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast_from!/4","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.broadcast_from!/4","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#call/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.call/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the child specification to start the endpoint\nunder a supervision tree.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#child_spec/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.child_spec/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the endpoint configuration for `key`\n\nReturns `default` if the key does not exist.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#config/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.config/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Reloads the configuration given the application environment changes.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#config_change/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.config_change/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the host for the given endpoint.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#host/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.host/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.init/1 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#init/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.init/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.local_broadcast/3 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#local_broadcast/3","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.local_broadcast/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.local_broadcast_from/4 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#local_broadcast_from/4","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.local_broadcast_from/4","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates the path information when routing to this endpoint.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#path/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.path/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates the script name.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#script_name/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.script_name/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the address and port that the server is running on","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#server_info/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.server_info/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Starts the endpoint supervision tree.\n\nAll other options are merged into the endpoint configuration.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#start_link/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.start_link/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a base64-encoded cryptographic hash (sha512) to a static file\nin `priv/static`. Meant to be used for Subresource Integrity with CDNs.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#static_integrity/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.static_integrity/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns a two item tuple with the first item being the `static_path`\nand the second item being the `static_integrity`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#static_lookup/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.static_lookup/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a route to a static file in `priv/static`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#static_path/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.static_path/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates the static URL without any path information.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:static_url` to generate\nsuch. It falls back to `:url` if `:static_url` is not set.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#static_url/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.static_url/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates the endpoint base URL but as a `URI` struct.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:url` to generate such.\nUseful for manipulating the URL data and passing it to\nURL helpers.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#struct_url/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.struct_url/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.subscribe/2 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#subscribe/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.subscribe/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.unsubscribe/1 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#unsubscribe/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.unsubscribe/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates the endpoint base URL without any path information.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:url` to generate such.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.html#url/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Endpoint.url/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"This module is invoked by your endpoint in case of errors on HTML requests.\n\nSee config/config.exs.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorHTML.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorHTML","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorHTML.html#render/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorHTML.render/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"This module is invoked by your endpoint in case of errors on JSON requests.\n\nSee config/config.exs.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorJSON.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorJSON","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorJSON.html#render/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.ErrorJSON.render/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"A module providing Internationalization with a gettext-based API.\n\nBy using [Gettext](https://hexdocs.pm/gettext), your module compiles translations\nthat you can use in your application. To use this Gettext backend module,\ncall `use Gettext` and pass it as an option:\n\n    use Gettext, backend: AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext\n\n    # Simple translation\n    gettext(\"Here is the string to translate\")\n\n    # Plural translation\n    ngettext(\"Here is the string to translate\",\n             \"Here are the strings to translate\",\n             3)\n\n    # Domain-based translation\n    dgettext(\"errors\", \"Here is the error message to translate\")\n\nSee the [Gettext Docs](https://hexdocs.pm/gettext) for detailed usage.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext","type":"module"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Gettext.Backend.handle_missing_bindings/2 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.html#handle_missing_bindings/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.handle_missing_bindings/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Gettext.Backend.handle_missing_plural_translation/7 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.html#handle_missing_plural_translation/7","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.handle_missing_plural_translation/7","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Gettext.Backend.handle_missing_translation/5 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.html#handle_missing_translation/5","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Gettext.handle_missing_translation/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"This module holds layouts and related functionality\nused by your application.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts","type":"module"},{"doc":"Renders your app layout.\n\nThis function is typically invoked from every template,\nand it often contains your application menu, sidebar,\nor similar.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#app/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.app/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Content","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#app/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.app/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `flash` (`:map`) (required) - the map of flash messages.\n* `current_scope` (`:map`) - the current [scope](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix/scopes.html). Defaults to `nil`.\n* `current_path` (`:string`) - the current request path. Defaults to `nil`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#app/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.app/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `inner_block` (required)","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#app/1-slots","title":"Slots - AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.app/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Shows the flash group with standard titles and content.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#flash_group/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.flash_group/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"<.flash_group flash={@flash} />","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#flash_group/1-examples","title":"Examples - AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.flash_group/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"* `flash` (`:map`) (required) - the map of flash messages.\n* `id` (`:string`) - the optional id of flash container. Defaults to `\"flash-group\"`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#flash_group/1-attributes","title":"Attributes - AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.flash_group/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#root/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.root/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Provides dark vs light theme toggle based on themes defined in app.css.\n\nSee   in root.html.heex which applies the theme before page load.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.html#theme_toggle/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Layouts.theme_toggle/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageController.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageController","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageController.html#home/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageController.home/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageController.html#run/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageController.run/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"This module contains pages rendered by PageController.\n\nSee the `page_html` directory for all templates available.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageHTML.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PageHTML","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PipelineBuilderLive.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PipelineBuilderLive","type":"module"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.LiveView.render/1 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PipelineBuilderLive.html#render/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.PipelineBuilderLive.render/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html#api/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.api/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html#browser/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.browser/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback invoked by Plug on every request.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html#call/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.call/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.VerifiedRoutes.formatted_routes/1 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html#formatted_routes/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.formatted_routes/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback required by Plug that initializes the router\nfor serving web requests.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html#init/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.init/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.VerifiedRoutes.verified_route?/2 .","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.html#verified_route?/2","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Router.verified_route?/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.html","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry","type":"module"},{"doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.html#child_spec/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.child_spec/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.html#metrics/0","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.metrics/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.html#start_link/1","title":"AttractorPhoenixWeb.Telemetry.start_link/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Enforces the minimum coverage threshold configured in `coveralls.json`.\n\nThis task expects `mix coveralls.json` to have been run already so that\n`cover/excoveralls.json` exists.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Coverage.Gate.html","title":"mix coverage.gate","type":"task"},{"doc":"Minimal fallback backend used by `AttractorEx.Handlers.Codergen` in tests and demos.","ref":"AttractorEx.SimulationBackend.html","title":"AttractorEx.SimulationBackend","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.SimulationBackend.html#run/3","title":"AttractorEx.SimulationBackend.run/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Public entry point for the AttractorEx pipeline engine.\n\n`AttractorEx` exposes the stable API for parsing, validating, executing, resuming,\nand serving DOT-defined Attractor pipelines.","ref":"AttractorEx.html","title":"AttractorEx","type":"module"},{"doc":"- `run/3` executes a new pipeline\n- `resume/3` resumes from a checkpoint\n- `validate/2` returns diagnostics without execution\n- `validate_or_raise/2` escalates validation errors\n- `start_http_server/1` exposes the engine over HTTP","ref":"AttractorEx.html#module-main-apis","title":"Main APIs - AttractorEx","type":"module"},{"doc":"Resumes execution from a checkpoint struct, map, or `checkpoint.json` path.","ref":"AttractorEx.html#resume/3","title":"AttractorEx.resume/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Parses, validates, and executes a pipeline graph from scratch.","ref":"AttractorEx.html#run/3","title":"AttractorEx.run/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Starts the lightweight Bandit-backed AttractorEx HTTP service.","ref":"AttractorEx.html#start_http_server/1","title":"AttractorEx.start_http_server/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Stops a previously started AttractorEx HTTP server.","ref":"AttractorEx.html#stop_http_server/1","title":"AttractorEx.stop_http_server/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Validates a DOT string or normalized graph and returns diagnostics.","ref":"AttractorEx.html#validate/2","title":"AttractorEx.validate/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Validates a DOT string or graph and raises on error-severity diagnostics.","ref":"AttractorEx.html#validate_or_raise/2","title":"AttractorEx.validate_or_raise/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Evaluates the compact condition-expression language used on pipeline edges.\n\nSupported features include truthy path checks, equality and inequality, numeric\ncomparisons, `&&` clause chaining, and nested map access with dot notation.","ref":"AttractorEx.Condition.html","title":"AttractorEx.Condition","type":"module"},{"doc":"Evaluates a condition string against the current execution context.","ref":"AttractorEx.Condition.html#evaluate/2","title":"AttractorEx.Condition.evaluate/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns whether an expression parses successfully.","ref":"AttractorEx.Condition.html#valid?/1","title":"AttractorEx.Condition.valid?/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Core execution engine for AttractorEx pipelines.\n\nThis module owns graph transformation, validation, handler dispatch, checkpointing,\nruntime event emission, retry logic, goal-gate enforcement, and edge selection.","ref":"AttractorEx.Engine.html","title":"AttractorEx.Engine","type":"module"},{"doc":"Resumes execution from a checkpoint file, map, or `AttractorEx.Checkpoint`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Engine.html#resume/3","title":"AttractorEx.Engine.resume/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Parses, validates, and executes a DOT pipeline.","ref":"AttractorEx.Engine.html#run/3","title":"AttractorEx.Engine.run/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Parses the supported Attractor DOT subset into `AttractorEx.Graph`.\n\nThe parser focuses on the executable subset used by the engine rather than full\nGraphviz grammar parity. It also finalizes parsed graphs by applying model stylesheet\nrules and normalizing nodes into runtime structs.","ref":"AttractorEx.Parser.html","title":"AttractorEx.Parser","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Parser.html#t:parse_scope/0","title":"AttractorEx.Parser.parse_scope/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Parses DOT source into a normalized `AttractorEx.Graph`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Parser.html#parse/1","title":"AttractorEx.Parser.parse/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Serializes handler outcomes into the `status.json` artifact contract.\n\nThe payload shape is aligned with the Appendix C-style status fields used by the\nupstream Attractor documentation while preserving a few backward-compatible aliases.","ref":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.html","title":"AttractorEx.StatusContract","type":"module"},{"doc":"Builds a normalized runtime map representation of an outcome.","ref":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.html#serialize_outcome/1","title":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.serialize_outcome/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds the on-disk status-file payload for an outcome.","ref":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.html#status_file_payload/1","title":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.status_file_payload/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Writes a pretty-printed `status.json` payload to disk.","ref":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.html#write_status_file/2","title":"AttractorEx.StatusContract.write_status_file/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Validates parsed graphs against the supported Attractor runtime contract.\n\nValidation covers structural errors, routing issues, handler-specific attributes,\nhuman-gate metadata, retry configuration, and model stylesheet linting.","ref":"AttractorEx.Validator.html","title":"AttractorEx.Validator","type":"module"},{"doc":"Finds the normalized start node ID for a graph, if present.","ref":"AttractorEx.Validator.html#start_node_id/1","title":"AttractorEx.Validator.start_node_id/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns all diagnostics for a normalized graph.","ref":"AttractorEx.Validator.html#validate/2","title":"AttractorEx.Validator.validate/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Validates a graph and raises when error-severity diagnostics are present.","ref":"AttractorEx.Validator.html#validate_or_raise/2","title":"AttractorEx.Validator.validate_or_raise/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Serializable checkpoint snapshot for resumable pipeline execution.\n\nThe engine writes checkpoints after every stage and accepts them again through\n`AttractorEx.resume/3`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Checkpoint.html","title":"AttractorEx.Checkpoint","type":"module"},{"doc":"Builds a checkpoint using the current UTC timestamp.","ref":"AttractorEx.Checkpoint.html#new/3","title":"AttractorEx.Checkpoint.new/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Runtime representation of a directed edge between two nodes.\n\nIn addition to the raw attribute map, edges expose normalized `condition` and\n`status` fields used directly by the routing logic in `AttractorEx.Engine`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Edge.html","title":"AttractorEx.Edge","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Edge.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Edge.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Builds a normalized edge struct from raw DOT attributes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Edge.html#new/3","title":"AttractorEx.Edge.new/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalized in-memory representation of a parsed pipeline graph.\n\nA graph carries graph-level attributes, node and edge defaults, a node map, and a\nflat edge list. `AttractorEx.Parser` produces this struct, `AttractorEx.Validator`\nchecks it, and `AttractorEx.Engine` executes it.","ref":"AttractorEx.Graph.html","title":"AttractorEx.Graph","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Graph.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Graph.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Parses and applies the `model_stylesheet` graph attribute.\n\nAttractorEx supports both legacy JSON-style stylesheets and a CSS-like selector\nsyntax. Styles are resolved before validation so the validator and engine see the\nsame effective node attributes.","ref":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.html","title":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.html#t:lint_diagnostic/0","title":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.lint_diagnostic/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.html#t:rule/0","title":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.rule/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Resolves the effective stylesheet attributes for a node.","ref":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.html#attrs_for_node/3","title":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.attrs_for_node/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns non-fatal stylesheet diagnostics.","ref":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.html#lint/1","title":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.lint/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Parses a stylesheet definition into ranked rules.","ref":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.html#parse/1","title":"AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet.parse/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Runtime representation of a pipeline node.\n\nNodes keep the original attribute map and the normalized fields that drive execution,\nsuch as shape, handler type, prompt, goal-gate status, and retry targets.","ref":"AttractorEx.Node.html","title":"AttractorEx.Node","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Node.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Node.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Returns the default handler type implied by a Graphviz shape.","ref":"AttractorEx.Node.html#handler_type_for_shape/1","title":"AttractorEx.Node.handler_type_for_shape/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Node.html#new/2","title":"AttractorEx.Node.new/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Standard result value returned by node handlers.\n\nOutcomes tell the engine whether a stage succeeded, partially succeeded, failed, or\nshould be retried. They also carry context updates and routing hints such as\n`preferred_label` and `suggested_next_ids`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#t:failure_category/0","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.failure_category/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#t:status/0","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.status/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Builds a failure outcome with a reason and failure category.","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#fail/2","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.fail/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a partial-success outcome with optional context updates and notes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#partial_success/2","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.partial_success/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a retry outcome with a reason and retry category.","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#retry/2","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.retry/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a success outcome with optional context updates and notes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Outcome.html#success/2","title":"AttractorEx.Outcome.success/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Behaviour implemented by all executable node handlers.\n\nHandlers receive the normalized node, current context, full graph, stage directory,\nand runtime options, and must return an `AttractorEx.Outcome`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handler.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handler","type":"behaviour"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Handler.html#c:execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handler.execute/5","type":"callback"},{"doc":"Resolves node types to executable handler modules.\n\nThe registry includes the built-in handlers required by the runtime and supports\ndynamic extension through `register/2`.","ref":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.html","title":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry","type":"module"},{"doc":"Alias for `resolve/1`.","ref":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.html#handler_for/1","title":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.handler_for/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns whether a type string is known to the registry.","ref":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.html#known_type?/1","title":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.known_type?/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Registers a handler module for an explicit type string.","ref":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.html#register/2","title":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.register/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Resolves the effective handler module for a node.","ref":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.html#resolve/1","title":"AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry.resolve/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for LLM-driven `codergen` stages.\n\nCodergen nodes derive their prompt from `prompt` or `label`, write prompt and\nresponse artifacts, and can run through either the unified LLM client layer or a\nlegacy backend module.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Codergen.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Codergen","type":"module"},{"doc":"Executes a codergen node and returns an `AttractorEx.Outcome`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Codergen.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Codergen.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for explicit conditional nodes.\n\nThe node itself succeeds immediately. Branch selection happens later when the engine\nevaluates outgoing edge conditions.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Conditional.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Conditional","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Conditional.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Conditional.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Fallback handler used when a node type does not need special runtime behavior.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Default.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Default","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Default.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Default.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for terminal `exit` nodes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Exit.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Exit","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Exit.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Exit.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for parallel branch fan-out nodes.\n\nIt executes each outgoing branch through a configurable branch runner and aggregates\nthe branch results according to the configured join policy.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Parallel.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Parallel","type":"module"},{"doc":"Executes all parallel branches and aggregates their outcomes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Parallel.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Parallel.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for `parallel.fan_in` nodes that select a best branch result.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.ParallelFanIn.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.ParallelFanIn","type":"module"},{"doc":"Evaluates prior parallel results and selects the best candidate.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.ParallelFanIn.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.ParallelFanIn.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for manager-loop nodes that observe and steer a child workflow.\n\nThe current implementation focuses on polling, stop conditions, and configurable\nobserve and steer hooks.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.StackManagerLoop.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.StackManagerLoop","type":"module"},{"doc":"Runs the manager loop until the child succeeds, fails, or a stop condition fires.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.StackManagerLoop.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.StackManagerLoop.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for the synthetic `start` node.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Start.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Start","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Start.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Start.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for shell-command tool nodes.\n\nThe handler runs the configured command on the local host, captures stdout and stderr,\nand optionally executes pre- and post-hook commands declared at graph level.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Tool.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Tool","type":"module"},{"doc":"Executes a tool node and returns the command output in context updates.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Tool.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.Tool.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Handler for `wait.human` nodes.\n\nIt collects available choices, resolves an answer from context or an interviewer\nadapter, normalizes that answer, and returns routing hints for the engine.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.WaitForHuman.html","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.WaitForHuman","type":"module"},{"doc":"Executes a human-gate node against a graph-aware set of outgoing choices.","ref":"AttractorEx.Handlers.WaitForHuman.html#execute/5","title":"AttractorEx.Handlers.WaitForHuman.execute/5","type":"function"},{"doc":"Helper functions for building and matching `wait.human` choices.\n\nThis module converts outgoing edges into normalized selectable options and performs\ntolerant matching against keys, labels, and destination node IDs.","ref":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.html","title":"AttractorEx.HumanGate","type":"module"},{"doc":"Builds the available choices for a human-gate node from its outgoing edges.","ref":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.html#choices_for/2","title":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.choices_for/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Finds the first matching choice for a human answer token.","ref":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.html#match_choice/2","title":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.match_choice/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalizes answer tokens for case-insensitive matching.","ref":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.html#normalize_token/1","title":"AttractorEx.HumanGate.normalize_token/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Behaviour for human-in-the-loop adapters used by `wait.human`.\n\nInterviewers can source answers from a console, queue, callback, HTTP workflow, or\nany custom adapter that implements the callbacks below.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewer","type":"behaviour"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.html#c:ask/4","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.ask/4","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.html#c:ask_multiple/4","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.ask_multiple/4","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.html#c:inform/4","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewer.inform/4","type":"callback"},{"doc":"Deterministic interviewer that auto-selects a configured answer or the first choice.\n\nThis adapter is mainly useful for tests and non-interactive automation.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.AutoApprove.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.AutoApprove","type":"module"},{"doc":"Interviewer that delegates question handling to caller-provided functions.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Callback.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Callback","type":"module"},{"doc":"Terminal-backed interviewer for local manual runs.\n\nIt prints normalized question metadata and accepts either plain text or JSON-shaped\nanswers.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Console.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Console","type":"module"},{"doc":"Shared question and answer normalization for interviewer adapters.\n\nThis module keeps console, queue, callback, recording, and HTTP interviewers on the\nsame wire format so `wait.human` behavior stays consistent across transports.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload","type":"module"},{"doc":"Builds a structured answer payload including matched options.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#answer_payload/2","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.answer_payload/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Extracts the answer field from common structured answer payload shapes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#extract_answer/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.extract_answer/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the preferred input mode for the normalized question.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#input_mode/3","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.input_mode/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Extracts a displayable message from an interviewer payload.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#message/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.message/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns whether a node is configured for multi-select input.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#multiple_choice?/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.multiple_choice?/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalizes a single choice map into the shared interviewer shape.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#normalize_choice/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.normalize_choice/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalizes an answer for multi-select questions.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#normalize_multiple_answer/2","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.normalize_multiple_answer/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalizes an answer for single-select questions.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#normalize_single_answer/2","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.normalize_single_answer/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalizes arbitrary answer values into comparable tokens.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#normalize_token/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.normalize_token/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Parses console input, decoding JSON objects and arrays when present.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#parse_console_input/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.parse_console_input/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds the normalized question payload for a human-gate node.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#question/3","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Infers the interviewer question type from node metadata and choice shape.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#question_type/2","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.question_type/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns whether a human answer is required for the node.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#required?/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.required?/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalizes timeout values such as `30s`, `5m`, or `1d` into milliseconds.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.html#timeout_ms/1","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload.timeout_ms/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Interviewer backed by a list or `Agent` queue of pre-seeded answers.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Queue.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Queue","type":"module"},{"doc":"Decorator interviewer that records questions, answers, and info payloads.\n\n`Recording` wraps another interviewer and forwards the interaction while emitting\nstructured events to a sink function or `Agent`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Recording.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Recording","type":"module"},{"doc":"HTTP-oriented interviewer used by `AttractorEx.HTTP`.\n\nQuestions are registered with `AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager`, exposed as pending HTTP\nresources, and completed when an external client submits an answer.","ref":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Server.html","title":"AttractorEx.Interviewers.Server","type":"module"},{"doc":"Convenience entry point for starting and stopping the AttractorEx HTTP service.\n\nThe service is composed of `AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager`, a `Registry`, and a Bandit\nserver running `AttractorEx.HTTP.Router`.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.html","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP","type":"module"},{"doc":"Starts the HTTP manager, registry, and Bandit server.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.html#start_server/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.start_server/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Stops a running HTTP server process or named server.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.html#stop_server/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.stop_server/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders parsed graphs into presentation-friendly HTTP formats.\n\nSupported outputs include SVG, JSON, Mermaid, and plain text summaries.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.html","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer","type":"module"},{"doc":"Renders a graph as structured JSON.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.html#to_json/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.to_json/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a graph as Mermaid flowchart text.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.html#to_mermaid/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.to_mermaid/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a graph as an SVG card-style diagram.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.html#to_svg/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.to_svg/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Renders a graph as a plain-text summary.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.html#to_text/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer.to_text/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"GenServer that owns the in-memory state for HTTP-managed pipeline runs.\n\nIt tracks pipeline status, events, checkpoints, pending human questions, and event\nsubscribers, and acts as the coordination point between the engine and the router.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#cancel/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.cancel/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#child_spec/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.child_spec/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Creates and starts a pipeline run under HTTP management.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#create_pipeline/4","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.create_pipeline/4","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#get_pipeline/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.get_pipeline/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#list_pipelines/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.list_pipelines/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#pending_questions/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.pending_questions/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#pipeline_checkpoint/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.pipeline_checkpoint/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#pipeline_context/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.pipeline_context/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#pipeline_events/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.pipeline_events/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#pipeline_graph/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.pipeline_graph/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#record_event/3","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.record_event/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#register_question/3","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.register_question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Starts the HTTP pipeline manager.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#start_link/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.start_link/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#submit_answer/4","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.submit_answer/4","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#subscribe/3","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.subscribe/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.html#timeout_question/3","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager.timeout_question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Plug router exposing the AttractorEx HTTP API.\n\nThe router supports pipeline creation, status polling, SSE event streams, graph\nrenderings, question answering, cancellation, checkpoint inspection, and context\ninspection.","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Router.html","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Router","type":"module"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Router.html#call/2","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Router.call/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.init/1 .","ref":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Router.html#init/1","title":"AttractorEx.HTTP.Router.init/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Phoenix-facing adapter layer for `AttractorEx`.\n\n`AttractorEx` remains the standalone pipeline engine. `AttractorExPhx` is the\nintegration seam a Phoenix application can depend on for:\n\n- direct pipeline execution via `run/3`\n- supervision-friendly HTTP server startup via `child_spec/1` and `start_link/1`\n- Req-based access to the HTTP control plane via `AttractorExPhx.Client`","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html","title":"AttractorExPhx","type":"module"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.answer_pipeline_question/3 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#answer_pipeline_question/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.answer_pipeline_question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.answer_question/3 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#answer_question/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.answer_question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.cancel_pipeline/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#cancel_pipeline/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.cancel_pipeline/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#child_spec/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.child_spec/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.create_pipeline/3 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#create_pipeline/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.create_pipeline/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_checkpoint/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_checkpoint/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_checkpoint/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_context/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_context/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_context/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_events/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_events/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_events/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph/2 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_graph/2","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_dot/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_graph_dot/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph_dot/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_json/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_graph_json/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph_json/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_mermaid/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_graph_mermaid/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph_mermaid/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_svg/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_graph_svg/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph_svg/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_text/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_graph_text/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph_text/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_questions/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_pipeline_questions/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_questions/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.get_status/1 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#get_status/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.get_status/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.list_pipelines/0 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#list_pipelines/0","title":"AttractorExPhx.list_pipelines/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#run/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.run/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"See  AttractorExPhx.Client.run_pipeline/3 .","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#run_pipeline/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.run_pipeline/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#start_http_server/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.start_http_server/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#start_link/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.start_link/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.html#stop_http_server/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.stop_http_server/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Req-based client for the `AttractorEx` HTTP control plane.\n\nThis module is intentionally Phoenix-friendly: LiveViews, controllers, and other\nOTP processes can call it without depending on `AttractorPhoenix`-specific glue.","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#answer_pipeline_question/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.answer_pipeline_question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#answer_question/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.answer_question/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#cancel_pipeline/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.cancel_pipeline/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#create_pipeline/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.create_pipeline/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_checkpoint/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_checkpoint/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_context/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_context/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_events/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_events/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_graph/2","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_graph_dot/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_dot/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_graph_json/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_json/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_graph_mermaid/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_mermaid/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_graph_svg/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_svg/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_graph_text/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_graph_text/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_pipeline_questions/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_pipeline_questions/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#get_status/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.get_status/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#list_pipelines/0","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.list_pipelines/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.Client.html#run_pipeline/3","title":"AttractorExPhx.Client.run_pipeline/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Supervision-friendly HTTP server wrapper for `AttractorEx`.\n\nPhoenix applications can place this child directly under their supervision tree to\nexpose the `AttractorEx` HTTP API alongside the web UI.","ref":"AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer.html","title":"AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer.html#child_spec/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer.child_spec/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer.html#start_link/1","title":"AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer.start_link/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Provider-agnostic LLM client used by codergen nodes and agent sessions.\n\nThe client resolves providers, applies middleware, delegates to adapter modules, and\nsupports both request/response and streaming flows.\n\nBeyond the low-level `complete/2` and `stream/2` APIs, the module also exposes:\n\n1. `from_env/1` for runtime construction from application config\n2. module-level default-client helpers\n3. spec-aligned convenience wrappers such as `generate/2`\n4. stream accumulation helpers for callers that want a final normalized response\n5. JSON object generation helpers layered on top of the normalized response surface","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#t:middleware/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.middleware/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Consumes a raw event stream and returns a normalized final response.\n\nThis is useful for callers that want provider streaming for latency but still need a\nsingle accumulated `AttractorEx.LLM.Response`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#accumulate_stream/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.accumulate_stream/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Consumes a raw event stream and returns a normalized final response.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#accumulate_stream/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.accumulate_stream/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Consumes a raw event stream and returns the accumulated response plus resolved request.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#accumulate_stream_with_request/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.accumulate_stream_with_request/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Clears the module-level default client.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#clear_default/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.clear_default/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a completion request via the configured module-level default client.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#complete/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.complete/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a completion request and returns either a response or an error tuple.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#complete/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.complete/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a completion request and also returns the resolved request.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#complete_with_request/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.complete_with_request/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the configured module-level default client, or `nil`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#default/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.default/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a client from application config, with direct opts taking precedence.\n\nSupported config shape:\n\n    config :attractor_phoenix, :attractor_ex_llm,\n      providers: %{\"openai\" => MyApp.OpenAIAdapter},\n      default_provider: \"openai\"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#from_env/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.from_env/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Spec-style completion alias for `complete/2`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#generate/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Spec-style completion alias for `complete/2`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#generate/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a JSON object via the configured module-level default client.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#generate_object/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate_object/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a JSON object from a non-streaming response.\n\nThe response body is decoded from `response.text`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#generate_object/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate_object/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a JSON object from a non-streaming response and also returns transport data.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#generate_object_with_request/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate_object_with_request/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Spec-style completion alias for `complete_with_request/2`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#generate_with_request/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate_with_request/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a client from keyword options.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#new/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.new/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Stores a module-level default client used by the arity-1 helpers.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#put_default/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.put_default/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a streaming request via the configured module-level default client.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#stream/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.stream/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a streaming request and returns the event stream or an error tuple.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#stream/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.stream/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a JSON object from a streamed response via the default client.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#stream_object/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.stream_object/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a JSON object by first accumulating a streamed response.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#stream_object/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.stream_object/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Generates a JSON object by first accumulating a streamed response and also returns\nthe normalized response plus resolved request.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#stream_object_with_request/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.stream_object_with_request/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a streaming request and also returns the resolved request.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.html#stream_with_request/2","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Client.stream_with_request/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Unified chat message struct used in LLM requests.\n\n`content` remains backward compatible with plain strings, but can also carry a list\nof tagged content parts through `AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart`.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.html#t:content/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.content/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.html#t:role/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.role/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Returns the plain-text projection of a message content payload.\n\nText and thinking parts contribute their text directly. Tool, image, audio, document,\nand JSON parts are summarized into a stable textual marker for callers that still need\na rough size estimate or fallback prompt representation.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.html#content_text/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Message.content_text/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Tagged content part used by `AttractorEx.LLM.Message`.\n\nThe unified client still treats multimodal payloads as pass-through data for provider\nadapters, but this struct gives requests a stable representation for richer content.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart","type":"module"},{"doc":"Known content part kinds carried by the normalized message model.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart.html#t:part_type/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart.part_type/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Behaviour implemented by unified LLM provider adapters.\n\nAdapters translate a normalized `AttractorEx.LLM.Request` into a provider-native API\ncall and return a normalized `AttractorEx.LLM.Response` or stream of events.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.ProviderAdapter.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.ProviderAdapter","type":"behaviour"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.ProviderAdapter.html#c:complete/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.ProviderAdapter.complete/1","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.ProviderAdapter.html#c:stream/1","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.ProviderAdapter.stream/1","type":"callback"},{"doc":"Unified request struct for provider-agnostic LLM completions.\n\nThe data model is intentionally small and focuses on the fields currently required by\ncodergen nodes and the agent session layer.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Request.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Request","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Request.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Request.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Unified response struct returned by provider adapters.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Response.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Response","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Response.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Response.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Event struct used by streaming LLM adapters.\n\nEvents cover stream lifecycle markers, text and reasoning deltas, tool payloads, the\nfinal response, and error cases.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.StreamEvent.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.StreamEvent","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.StreamEvent.html#t:event_type/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.StreamEvent.event_type/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.StreamEvent.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.StreamEvent.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Normalized token-usage counters returned by LLM responses and streams.","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Usage.html","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Usage","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.LLM.Usage.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.LLM.Usage.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Applies `apply_patch` v4a-style filesystem updates against a local execution environment.\n\nThe implementation is intentionally conservative. It supports add, delete, update,\nand move operations using the appendix-style patch envelope and verifies update hunks\nagainst current file contents before writing changes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch.html#t:operation_result/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch.operation_result/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch.html#apply/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch.apply/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Built-in coding-agent tools backed by an `ExecutionEnvironment`.\n\nThe `:default` preset exposes a provider-neutral baseline toolset. Provider\npresets then layer provider-native tool names and argument shapes on top of\nthe same execution environment so OpenAI, Anthropic, and Gemini sessions can\nstay closer to their upstream agent harnesses. Gemini's optional web tools can\nalso be enabled for the `:gemini` preset.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools.html#t:preset/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools.preset/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools.html#for_provider/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools.for_provider/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Typed session event emitted by `AttractorEx.Agent.Session`.\n\nThe shape mirrors the coding-agent loop spec's session-event contract while\nkeeping a `payload` alias for backward compatibility with older callers.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.html#t:kind/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.kind/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.html#new/4","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.new/4","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.html#supported_kinds/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Event.supported_kinds/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Execution-environment behaviour for coding-agent sessions.\n\nThe contract intentionally mirrors the core local tooling surface exposed by\nthe agent loop: filesystem reads and writes, directory listing and globbing,\ntext search, shell command execution, and a small amount of host metadata.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment","type":"behaviour"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:environment_context/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.environment_context/1","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:glob/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.glob/2","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:grep/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.grep/3","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:list_directory/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.list_directory/2","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:platform/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.platform/1","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:read_file/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.read_file/2","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:shell_command/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.shell_command/3","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:working_directory/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.working_directory/1","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#c:write_file/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.write_file/3","type":"callback"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#environment_context/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.environment_context/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#glob/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.glob/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#grep/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.grep/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#implementation?/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.implementation?/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#list_directory/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.list_directory/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#platform/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.platform/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#read_file/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.read_file/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#shell_command/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.shell_command/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#working_directory/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.working_directory/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.html#write_file/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment.write_file/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Local filesystem-backed execution environment for agent sessions.\n\nIt exposes a working directory, platform information, and the built-in\nfilesystem/shell primitives used by the coding-agent loop.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Builds a local execution environment.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment.html#new/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment.new/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Provider-aligned configuration for the coding-agent loop.\n\nA profile packages a model, toolset, provider options, and an optional system-prompt\nbuilder so agent sessions can stay portable across providers. Profiles can also be\nextended with `register_tool/2` and `register_tools/2`, allowing custom tools to be\nlayered on top of provider presets while overriding name collisions deterministically.\n\nThe module also exposes a maintained cross-provider integration matrix for the\nbuilt-in OpenAI, Anthropic, and Gemini presets. Gemini can optionally include\nweb-search tools via `gemini(web_tools: true)`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#t:integration_entry/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.integration_entry/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#anthropic/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.anthropic/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds the system prompt for a session request.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#build_system_prompt/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.build_system_prompt/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#gemini/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.gemini/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the project-instruction files relevant to the active provider profile.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#instruction_files/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.instruction_files/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the maintained cross-provider integration matrix for built-in presets.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#integration_matrix/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.integration_matrix/0","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a provider profile from keyword options.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#new/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.new/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#openai/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.openai/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the provider-native request path associated with reasoning/thinking controls.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#reasoning_option_path/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.reasoning_option_path/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the upstream native tool names the preset is intended to align with.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#reference_tool_names/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.reference_tool_names/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Registers or replaces a tool on top of an existing profile.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#register_tool/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.register_tool/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Registers or replaces tools on top of an existing profile, preserving order.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#register_tools/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.register_tools/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the reference-agent prompt family used as the preset target.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#system_prompt_style/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.system_prompt_style/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Returns the serialized tool definitions exposed to the model.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.html#tool_definitions/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile.tool_definitions/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Stateful coding-agent loop built on top of `AttractorEx.LLM.Client`.\n\nA session owns request construction, conversation history, tool execution, tool\nresult truncation, steering and follow-up queues, loop detection, subagent\nlifecycle management, lifecycle events, and layered project-instruction discovery\nacross ancestor `AGENTS.md`/provider-specific docs with a shared 32 KB prompt budget.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#t:state/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.state/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#t:turn/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.turn/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Marks the session as aborted and closed.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#abort/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.abort/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Closes the session without aborting an in-flight tool.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#close/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.close/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Queues a follow-up user input to run after the current submission completes.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#follow_up/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.follow_up/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Builds a new coding-agent session.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#new/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.new/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Executes a session-managed subagent tool and returns `{output, updated_session}`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#run_subagent_tool/3","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.run_subagent_tool/3","type":"function"},{"doc":"Queues steering text to be injected on the next round.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#steer/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.steer/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Submits a user message into the agent loop.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.html#submit/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Session.submit/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Runtime configuration for coding-agent sessions.\n\nThis struct centralizes turn limits, tool-round limits, timeout policy, output\ntruncation policy, and loop-detection settings.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Builds a session config, merging tool output limit overrides with defaults.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig.html#new/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig.new/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Definition of a callable tool exposed to an agent session.\n\nTools default to `target: :environment`, meaning their executor receives the\ncurrent execution environment. Session-managed tools such as subagent lifecycle\noperations set `target: :session` and receive the current session instead.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.html#t:executor/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.executor/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.html#t:target/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.target/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Serializes a tool into the model-facing definition shape.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.html#definition/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.Tool.definition/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalized representation of a tool call requested by the model.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolCall.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolCall","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolCall.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolCall.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Lightweight registry of agent tools keyed by name.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Builds a registry map from a tool list.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.html#from_tools/1","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.from_tools/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"Fetches a tool by name.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.html#get/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.get/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Registers or replaces a tool in the registry.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.html#register/2","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry.register/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"Normalized representation of a tool execution result fed back to the model.","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolResult.html","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolResult","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolResult.html#t:t/0","title":"AttractorEx.Agent.ToolResult.t/0","type":"type"},{"doc":"Built-in graph transform that expands simple runtime variables such as `$goal`.","ref":"AttractorEx.Transforms.VariableExpansion.html","title":"AttractorEx.Transforms.VariableExpansion","type":"module"},{"doc":"","ref":"AttractorEx.Transforms.VariableExpansion.html#transform/1","title":"AttractorEx.Transforms.VariableExpansion.transform/1","type":"function"},{"doc":"# AttractorEx Overview\n\n`AttractorEx` is the standalone pipeline engine embedded in this Phoenix project. It implements a practical, execution-oriented subset of the [strongDM Attractor specification](https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/attractor-spec.md) and extends it with an HTTP control plane, human-in-the-loop adapters, a unified LLM client layer, and a coding-agent session model.","ref":"overview.html","title":"AttractorEx Overview","type":"extras"},{"doc":"At a high level, `AttractorEx` turns DOT graphs into executable workflows:\n\n1. Parse a DOT graph into a normalized runtime model.\n2. Validate structural, routing, and handler-specific constraints.\n3. Execute nodes from `start` to `exit`.\n4. Route across edges by condition, status, preferred labels, or suggested next IDs.\n5. Persist status artifacts, checkpoints, and per-stage outputs.","ref":"overview.html#what-it-does","title":"What It Does - AttractorEx Overview","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The library is organized into a small set of focused layers:\n\n| Layer | Main modules | Responsibility |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Entry points | `AttractorEx`, `AttractorEx.Engine` | Public API and execution orchestration |\n| DOT model | `AttractorEx.Parser`, `AttractorEx.Graph`, `AttractorEx.Node`, `AttractorEx.Edge` | Parse and normalize the graph |\n| Validation | `AttractorEx.Validator`, `AttractorEx.Condition`, `AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet` | Linting, schema checks, and selector-based styling |\n| Runtime handlers | `AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry`, `AttractorEx.Handlers.*` | Node execution semantics |\n| Human gates | `AttractorEx.HumanGate`, `AttractorEx.Interviewer`, `AttractorEx.Interviewers.*` | `wait.human` workflows and answer normalization |\n| HTTP service | `AttractorEx.HTTP`, `AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager`, `AttractorEx.HTTP.Router` | Remote pipeline execution and SSE updates |\n| Phoenix adapter | `AttractorExPhx`, `AttractorExPhx.Client`, `AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer` | Phoenix-facing integration seam over the standalone engine |\n| Unified LLM | `AttractorEx.LLM.*` | Provider-agnostic completion and streaming |\n| Agent loop | `AttractorEx.Agent.*` | Spec-inspired coding-agent session primitives |","ref":"overview.html#architecture","title":"Architecture - AttractorEx Overview","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.run/3` follows the same broad lifecycle documented in the upstream spec:\n\n1. Parse DOT input.\n2. Apply built-in and custom graph transforms.\n3. Validate the transformed graph.\n4. Create a run directory and manifest.\n5. Execute node handlers one step at a time.\n6. Write `status.json` and `checkpoint.json` artifacts.\n7. Emit structured events for observers and the HTTP service.","ref":"overview.html#core-execution-flow","title":"Core Execution Flow - AttractorEx Overview","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Each run writes runtime artifacts under the configured logs root:\n\n- `manifest.json` for run metadata.\n- `checkpoint.json` for resumable state.\n- `status.json` for per-stage and final outcome serialization.\n- Handler-specific files such as `prompt.md`, `response.md`, and tool hook logs.","ref":"overview.html#output-artifacts","title":"Output Artifacts - AttractorEx Overview","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The rest of this documentation is structured to match how the code is used:\n\n- [Pipeline Engine](pipeline-engine.html) for graph execution semantics.\n- [Human-in-the-Loop](human-in-the-loop.html) for `wait.human` flows.\n- [HTTP API](http-api.html) for service mode and transport contracts.\n- [Agent Loop](agent-loop.html) for coding-agent session primitives.\n- [Spec Alignment](spec-alignment.html) for implementation status against the upstream documents.\n\nFor source-level details, browse the grouped module documentation in the sidebar.","ref":"overview.html#reading-the-docs","title":"Reading The Docs - AttractorEx Overview","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Pipeline Engine","ref":"pipeline-engine.html","title":"Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The primary entry points are:\n\n- `AttractorEx.run/3`\n- `AttractorEx.resume/3`\n- `AttractorEx.validate/2`\n- `AttractorEx.validate_or_raise/2`\n\n`run/3` executes a pipeline from its start node. `resume/3` restores execution from a checkpoint map, struct, or `checkpoint.json` path.","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#public-api","title":"Public API - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The parser converts DOT into these runtime structs:\n\n- `AttractorEx.Graph`\n- `AttractorEx.Node`\n- `AttractorEx.Edge`\n\nThis model is intentionally smaller than full Graphviz DOT. It prioritizes the subset needed to execute Attractor-style workflows reliably.","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#dot-model","title":"DOT Model - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Node execution is determined by either an explicit `type` attribute or the node shape:\n\n| Shape | Default handler type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Mdiamond` | `start` |\n| `Msquare` | `exit` |\n| `diamond` | `conditional` |\n| `component` | `parallel` |\n| `tripleoctagon` | `parallel.fan_in` |\n| `hexagon` | `wait.human` |\n| `parallelogram` | `tool` |\n| `house` | `stack.manager_loop` |\n| `box` | `codergen` |\n\nYou can override this with `type=\"...\"`, and you can register new handler modules through `AttractorEx.HandlerRegistry`.","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#handler-mapping","title":"Handler Mapping - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The engine selects the next edge in this order:\n\n1. Matching `condition=...`\n2. Matching `status=...`\n3. Matching the handler outcome's `preferred_label`\n4. Matching the handler outcome's `suggested_next_ids`\n5. Unconditional edge by weight\n6. Lexical fallback\n\nThis is implemented in `AttractorEx.Engine` and matches the spec-driven behavior documented in the local compliance notes.","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#routing-rules","title":"Routing Rules - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.Engine` supports:\n\n- Node retry policies with exponential backoff.\n- Graph-level and node-level retry targets.\n- Goal-gate nodes that must end in success or partial success.\n- Loop restart semantics via edge metadata.\n\nOutcomes are represented as `AttractorEx.Outcome` values and serialized through `AttractorEx.StatusContract`.","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#retries-and-goal-gates","title":"Retries And Goal Gates - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Before validation and execution, the engine applies:\n\n1. Model stylesheet resolution through `AttractorEx.ModelStylesheet`\n2. Variable expansion through `AttractorEx.Transforms.VariableExpansion`\n3. Any custom graph transforms passed in `opts`\n\nAt runtime, codergen stages may also receive synthesized context carryover text based on fidelity settings.","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#styling-and-transforms","title":"Styling And Transforms - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"For the precise implementation details:\n\n- `AttractorEx.Engine` for orchestration\n- `AttractorEx.Validator` for lint rules\n- `AttractorEx.Handlers.*` for node behavior\n- `AttractorEx.StatusContract` for artifact payloads","ref":"pipeline-engine.html#recommended-reading","title":"Recommended Reading - Pipeline Engine","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Phoenix Adapter\n\n`AttractorEx` stays framework-agnostic. `AttractorExPhx` is the explicit adapter layer that plugs Phoenix into the engine.","ref":"phoenix-adapter.html","title":"Phoenix Adapter","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The repository now has three clearer boundaries:\n\n1. `AttractorEx` for the standalone engine, HTTP service, and spec-facing runtime behavior.\n2. `AttractorExPhx` for Phoenix-oriented integration code such as supervision-friendly server startup and Req-based HTTP access.\n3. `AttractorPhoenixWeb` for the UI and controller/liveview experience.\n\nThat split keeps `lib/attractor_ex/` independent while making the integration path easy to find and test on its own.","ref":"phoenix-adapter.html#why-this-layer-exists","title":"Why This Layer Exists - Phoenix Adapter","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- `AttractorExPhx`\n- `AttractorExPhx.Client`\n- `AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer`","ref":"phoenix-adapter.html#main-modules","title":"Main Modules - Phoenix Adapter","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Start the engine HTTP API under a Phoenix supervision tree:\n\n```elixir\nchildren = [\n  {AttractorExPhx.HTTPServer,\n   port: 4101,\n   ip: {127, 0, 0, 1},\n   manager: MyApp.AttractorHTTP.Manager,\n   registry: MyApp.AttractorHTTP.Registry,\n   name: MyApp.AttractorHTTPServer}\n]\n```\n\nRun a pipeline directly from a Phoenix controller or other process:\n\n```elixir\n{:ok, result} = AttractorExPhx.run(dot_source, %{}, logs_root: \"tmp/runs\")\n```\n\nCall the HTTP control plane from LiveView:\n\n```elixir\n{:ok, %{\"pipelines\" => pipelines}} = AttractorExPhx.list_pipelines()\n{:ok, %{\"pipeline_id\" => id}} = AttractorExPhx.create_pipeline(dot_source, %{})\n{:ok, graph} = AttractorExPhx.get_pipeline_graph_json(id)\n```","ref":"phoenix-adapter.html#typical-usage","title":"Typical Usage - Phoenix Adapter","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The adapter has its own test scope under `test/attractor_ex_phx/` so the integration contract can be validated without depending on the LiveView UI tests to cover it indirectly.","ref":"phoenix-adapter.html#test-strategy","title":"Test Strategy - Phoenix Adapter","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Human-in-the-Loop\n\n`wait.human` is the AttractorEx mechanism for pausing pipeline execution until a person, service, or test adapter provides an answer.","ref":"human-in-the-loop.html","title":"Human-in-the-Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- `AttractorEx.Handlers.WaitForHuman`\n- `AttractorEx.HumanGate`\n- `AttractorEx.Interviewer`\n- `AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload`\n- `AttractorEx.Interviewers.*`","ref":"human-in-the-loop.html#core-modules","title":"Core Modules - Human-in-the-Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"When the engine reaches a `wait.human` node:\n\n1. Outgoing edges are converted into normalized choices.\n2. The runtime looks for an answer in context first.\n3. If no answer is present, an interviewer adapter is invoked.\n4. The answer is normalized into a single or multi-select payload.\n5. The handler returns an `AttractorEx.Outcome` with suggested next targets.","ref":"human-in-the-loop.html#flow","title":"Flow - Human-in-the-Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The library ships with several adapters:\n\n- `AutoApprove` for deterministic test or local automation flows.\n- `Console` for terminal-driven interaction.\n- `Callback` for embedding custom functions.\n- `Queue` for list- or `Agent`-backed scripted answers.\n- `Recording` for wrapping another interviewer while capturing events.\n- `Server` for HTTP-backed pending-question workflows.","ref":"human-in-the-loop.html#supported-interviewers","title":"Supported Interviewers - Human-in-the-Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.Interviewers.Payload` normalizes questions and answers into a shared contract with fields like:\n\n- `type`\n- `options`\n- `default`\n- `multiple`\n- `required`\n- `metadata.input_mode`\n\nThat shared shape is what allows the HTTP server, console adapter, tests, and custom callbacks to behave consistently.","ref":"human-in-the-loop.html#question-model","title":"Question Model - Human-in-the-Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`wait.human` supports:\n\n- direct choice keys\n- labels\n- node IDs\n- structured answer payloads\n- defaults on blank answers or timeouts\n- multi-select answers\n- skip and timeout signaling\n\nIf a response cannot be matched, the handler falls back to the first outgoing choice, which keeps the pipeline executable even under ambiguous input.","ref":"human-in-the-loop.html#routing-semantics","title":"Routing Semantics - Human-in-the-Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# HTTP API\n\n`AttractorEx.HTTP` exposes a lightweight Bandit-backed service for running pipelines remotely.","ref":"http-api.html","title":"HTTP API","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Start the service with:\n\n```elixir\n{:ok, pid} = AttractorEx.start_http_server(port: 4041)\n```\n\nThis starts:\n\n- `AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager` for pipeline state\n- a duplicate-key `Registry` for event subscribers\n- `AttractorEx.HTTP.Router` for the HTTP surface","ref":"http-api.html#main-entry-point","title":"Main Entry Point - HTTP API","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The router exposes these endpoints:\n\n- `POST /pipelines`\n- `GET /pipelines`\n- `GET /pipelines/:id`\n- `GET /pipelines/:id/events`\n- `POST /pipelines/:id/cancel`\n- `GET /pipelines/:id/graph`\n- `GET /pipelines/:id/questions`\n- `POST /pipelines/:id/questions/:qid/answer`\n- `GET /pipelines/:id/checkpoint`\n- `GET /pipelines/:id/context`\n\nIt also includes definition-of-done compatibility aliases:\n\n- `POST /run`\n- `GET /status`\n- `POST /answer`","ref":"http-api.html#primary-endpoints","title":"Primary Endpoints - HTTP API","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`GET /pipelines/:id/events` supports both:\n\n- JSON polling\n- server-sent events when streaming is enabled\n\nThe HTTP manager records engine events like:\n\n- `PipelineStarted`\n- `StageStarted`\n- `CheckpointSaved`\n- `StageCompleted`\n- `StageFailed`\n- `PipelineCompleted`\n- `PipelineFailed`","ref":"http-api.html#event-streaming","title":"Event Streaming - HTTP API","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`GET /pipelines/:id/graph` supports multiple formats:\n\n- `svg`\n- `dot`\n- `json`\n- `mermaid`\n- `text`\n\n`AttractorEx.HTTP.GraphRenderer` is responsible for the non-DOT renderings.","ref":"http-api.html#graph-rendering","title":"Graph Rendering - HTTP API","type":"extras"},{"doc":"When service mode is used, `AttractorEx.HTTP.Manager` runs pipelines with `AttractorEx.Interviewers.Server`, which means `wait.human` questions become pending HTTP resources that can be listed and answered out-of-process.","ref":"http-api.html#human-gate-integration","title":"Human Gate Integration - HTTP API","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Agent Loop\n\n`AttractorEx.Agent.*` implements a spec-inspired coding-agent session model on top of the unified LLM client.","ref":"agent-loop.html","title":"Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- `AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.Session`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.SessionConfig`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.Tool`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.ToolCall`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.ToolResult`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.ToolRegistry`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.ExecutionEnvironment`\n- `AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment`","ref":"agent-loop.html#main-modules","title":"Main Modules - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.Agent.Session` owns the loop:\n\n1. build a provider-aligned request\n2. send it through `AttractorEx.LLM.Client`\n3. normalize tool calls\n4. execute tools with timeouts and truncation rules\n5. feed tool results back into the next round\n\nThe session layer is deliberately conservative: it focuses on determinism, bounded output, and operational safety rather than full parity with every upstream provider feature.","ref":"agent-loop.html#responsibilities","title":"Responsibilities - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.Agent.Session` now emits a typed event stream through `AttractorEx.Agent.Event`.\n\nImplemented event kinds include:\n\n- `session_start`\n- `session_end`\n- `user_input`\n- `assistant_text_start`\n- `assistant_text_delta`\n- `assistant_text_end`\n- `tool_call_start`\n- `tool_call_output_delta`\n- `tool_call_end`\n- `steering_injected`\n- `turn_limit`\n- `loop_detection`\n- `error`\n\nFor non-streaming `Client.complete/2` responses and synchronous tool execution, the session synthesizes single-chunk delta events so host applications can still consume a consistent event surface. `tool_call_end` carries the full untruncated tool output for UI/logging integrations, while the model continues to receive the bounded/truncated tool result stored in conversation history.","ref":"agent-loop.html#event-surface","title":"Event Surface - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile` packages:\n\n- a provider ID\n- a model name\n- provider capability metadata such as reasoning support, streaming support, parallel tool-call support, and context-window size\n- tool definitions\n- provider options\n- a system prompt builder\n\nThis keeps the agent loop portable across LLM providers while letting each integration choose its own prompt and tool behavior.\n\nConvenience presets are available for the common coding-agent providers:\n\n- `ProviderProfile.openai/1`\n- `ProviderProfile.anthropic/1`\n- `ProviderProfile.gemini/1`\n\nThose presets attach provider-aligned built-in tool bundles and default capability metadata so applications do not need to rebuild the baseline profile shape manually.\n\n`ProviderProfile.integration_matrix/0` exposes the maintained cross-provider compatibility matrix for:\n\n- implemented tool names\n- upstream reference tool names\n- capability flags\n- provider-specific instruction files\n- reasoning/thinking option paths\n- shared session event kinds","ref":"agent-loop.html#provider-profiles","title":"Provider Profiles - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The environment contract now includes the local tool surface used by the coding-agent loop:\n\n- `working_directory/1`\n- `platform/1`\n- `read_file/2`\n- `write_file/3`\n- `list_directory/2`\n- `glob/2`\n- `grep/3`\n- `shell_command/3`\n- `environment_context/1`\n\n`AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment` is the default implementation used in tests and local sessions.","ref":"agent-loop.html#execution-environment","title":"Execution Environment - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.Agent.BuiltinTools` exposes a provider-neutral baseline toolset under the `:default` preset:\n\n- `read_file`\n- `write_file`\n- `list_directory`\n- `glob`\n- `grep`\n- `shell_command`\n- `spawn_agent`\n- `send_input`\n- `wait`\n- `close_agent`\n\nProvider presets now swap in provider-native tool names where the upstream agent harness differs:\n\n- OpenAI: `apply_patch`, `shell`\n- Anthropic: `edit_file`, `shell`\n- Gemini: `read_many_files`, `edit_file`, `shell`, `list_dir`\n\nFilesystem and shell tools are backed by the execution-environment behaviour, so alternative environments can swap in sandboxed or remote implementations without changing the session loop. The OpenAI-facing `apply_patch` tool is available for local sessions through `AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch`. Subagent tools are session-managed and create child `AttractorEx.Agent.Session` instances that keep independent history while sharing the parent's execution environment.","ref":"agent-loop.html#built-in-tools","title":"Built-In Tools - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The coding-agent loop now implements the spec's subagent lifecycle:\n\n- `spawn_agent` creates a child session, inherits the parent profile/tool bundle, optionally overrides model, working directory, and `max_turns`, and immediately runs the scoped task\n- `send_input` continues an existing child session with another message\n- `wait` returns a JSON payload containing subagent output, success, and turns used\n- `close_agent` removes the child session from the active subagent map\n\nSubagents inherit the parent's execution environment and are depth-limited by `SessionConfig.max_subagent_depth` (default `1`).","ref":"agent-loop.html#subagents","title":"Subagents - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The default system-prompt builder now includes:\n\n- working directory and platform\n- provider/model metadata\n- available tool names\n- serialized environment context\n- project instruction files discovered from the working directory ancestry\n\nProject instruction discovery loads `AGENTS.md` plus provider-specific files such as `CODEX.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, and `.codex/instructions.md` when present.","ref":"agent-loop.html#prompt-context","title":"Prompt Context - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The local coding-agent compliance guide tracks implemented and missing areas relative to the upstream coding-agent loop specification. Read the `Coding Agent Loop Compliance` reference for the detailed matrix.","ref":"agent-loop.html#compliance-status","title":"Compliance Status - Agent Loop","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Spec Alignment\n\n`AttractorEx` is built against the strongDM Attractor family of specifications, but it does not claim full parity with every upstream feature.","ref":"spec-alignment.html","title":"Spec Alignment","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- [Attractor specification](https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/attractor-spec.md)\n- [Coding-agent loop specification](https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/coding-agent-loop-spec.md)\n- [Unified LLM specification](https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/unified-llm-spec.md)","ref":"spec-alignment.html#upstream-sources","title":"Upstream Sources - Spec Alignment","type":"extras"},{"doc":"This repository keeps implementation-facing compliance reports under `lib/attractor_ex/`:\n\n- `ATTRACTOR_SPEC_COMPLIANCE.md`\n- `CODING_AGENT_LOOP_COMPLIANCE.md`\n- `UNIFIED_LLM_SPEC_COMPLIANCE.md`\n\nThose documents are included in the generated ExDoc output so the rendered docs expose both:\n\n- narrative architecture guides\n- section-by-section compliance detail","ref":"spec-alignment.html#local-reference-documents","title":"Local Reference Documents - Spec Alignment","type":"extras"},{"doc":"The highest-confidence parts of the implementation today are:\n\n- parser and validation coverage for the supported DOT subset\n- node execution and routing\n- human-in-the-loop flows\n- HTTP service mode\n- the low-level unified LLM client contract\n- the coding-agent loop's local tool/runtime contract, including subagent lifecycle support\n\nAreas explicitly documented as partial or not implemented remain partial or not implemented in the generated docs. The goal of this documentation set is to be accurate first, then polished.","ref":"spec-alignment.html#what-to-expect","title":"What To Expect - Spec Alignment","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# AttractorEx (Standalone Library)\n\n`AttractorEx` is the primary artifact in this repository.\n\nThis folder contains a DOT-driven pipeline engine inspired by strongDM Attractor:\n\n1. Parser (`Parser`)\n2. Validator (`Validator`)\n3. Execution engine (`Engine`)\n4. Routing and condition evaluator (`Condition`)\n5. Handler registry + built-in handlers (`Handlers.*`)","ref":"readme.html","title":"AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`lib/attractor_ex` does not depend on `AttractorPhoenix` or `AttractorPhoenixWeb` modules.\n\nDependency boundary:\n\n1. Internal references are only `AttractorEx.*`.\n2. Runtime deps used here are standard library + `Jason`.\n3. Phoenix-specific integration now lives in the separate `AttractorExPhx` adapter layer.\n4. Phoenix is used by the demo UI app, not by this library code.","ref":"readme.html#independence-from-phoenix-app","title":"Independence from Phoenix App - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"```elixir\nAttractorEx.run(dot_source, context_map, opts)\nAttractorEx.resume(dot_source, checkpoint_or_path, opts)\nAttractorEx.start_http_server(port: 4041)\n```\n\nExample:\n\n```elixir\ndot = \"\"\"\ndigraph attractor {\n  start [shape=Mdiamond]\n  hello [shape=parallelogram, tool_command=\"echo hello world\"]\n  done [shape=Msquare]\n  start -> hello\n  hello -> done\n}\n\"\"\"\n\n{:ok, result} = AttractorEx.run(dot, %{})\n\ncheckpoint_path = Path.join(result.logs_root, \"checkpoint.json\")\n{:ok, resumed} = AttractorEx.resume(dot, checkpoint_path, codergen_backend: MyApp.LLMBackend)\n\n{:ok, server_pid} = AttractorEx.start_http_server(port: 4041)\n```","ref":"readme.html#public-api","title":"Public API - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx.start_http_server/1` starts a lightweight Bandit-backed HTTP service around the engine.\n\nImplemented endpoints:\n\n1. `POST /pipelines`\n2. `GET /pipelines/:id`\n3. `GET /pipelines/:id/events`\n4. `POST /pipelines/:id/cancel`\n5. `GET /pipelines/:id/graph`\n6. `GET /pipelines/:id/questions`\n7. `POST /pipelines/:id/questions/:qid/answer`\n8. `GET /pipelines/:id/checkpoint`\n9. `GET /pipelines/:id/context`\n\nCompatibility aliases for the definition-of-done checklist:\n\n1. `POST /run` delegates to `POST /pipelines`\n2. `GET /status?pipeline_id=...` (or `?id=...`) delegates to `GET /pipelines/:id`\n3. `POST /answer` accepts `pipeline_id`, `question_id` (or `qid`), and `answer` (or `value`)\n\nGraph endpoint formats:\n\n1. Default: `GET /pipelines/:id/graph` returns a native SVG graph rendering.\n2. `GET /pipelines/:id/graph?format=dot` returns raw DOT.\n3. `GET /pipelines/:id/graph?format=json` returns parsed graph JSON.\n4. `GET /pipelines/:id/graph?format=mermaid` returns Mermaid flowchart text.\n5. `GET /pipelines/:id/graph?format=text` returns a plain-text graph summary.\n\nHTTP service hardening:\n\n1. Empty pipeline submissions are rejected with `400`.\n2. Unsupported graph formats are rejected with `400` and a supported-format list.\n3. Responses include `cache-control: no-store` and `x-content-type-options: nosniff`.\n4. JSON request parsing is limited to a 1 MB body by default.\n\nHuman-in-the-loop web flow:\n\n1. Submit a pipeline containing `wait.human`.\n2. Poll `GET /pipelines/:id/questions` for pending questions.\n3. Send a choice to `POST /pipelines/:id/questions/:qid/answer`.\n4. Subscribe to `GET /pipelines/:id/events` for SSE status updates.","ref":"readme.html#http-server-mode","title":"HTTP Server Mode - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"`AttractorEx` treats `box` nodes (or `type=\"codergen\"`) as LLM stages.\n\nHandler behavior:\n\n1. Prompt source: node `prompt` (fallback: node `label`).\n2. Variable expansion: `$goal` from graph-level `goal`.\n3. Preferred backend selection: `opts[:llm_client]` using unified LLM client.\n4. Legacy backend selection: `opts[:codergen_backend]`.\n5. Legacy backend contract: module with `run(node, prompt, context)` returning:\n   - `String` (will be written to `response.md`), or\n   - `%AttractorEx.Outcome{}` (full control of status/context updates).\n\nUnified client contract:\n\n1. Build client with providers map and optional default:\n   - `%AttractorEx.LLM.Client{providers: %{\"openai\" => MyAdapter}, default_provider: \"openai\"}`\n   - or `AttractorEx.LLM.Client.from_env/1` with:\n\n     ```elixir\n     config :attractor_phoenix, :attractor_ex_llm,\n       providers: %{\"openai\" => MyAdapter},\n       default_provider: \"openai\"\n     ```\n2. Adapter module contract:\n   - `complete(%AttractorEx.LLM.Request{}) :: %AttractorEx.LLM.Response{} | {:error, term()}`\n3. Node attrs used for unified request:\n   - `llm_model`, `llm_provider`, `reasoning_effort`, `max_tokens`, `temperature`\n4. Higher-level client helpers:\n   - `generate/2` and `generate_with_request/2`\n   - `accumulate_stream/2` to turn raw streaming events into a final `%AttractorEx.LLM.Response{}`\n   - `generate_object/2` and `stream_object/2` for JSON object decoding\n5. Message content:\n   - `AttractorEx.LLM.Message.content` accepts either plain text or a list of `AttractorEx.LLM.MessagePart` structs for richer multimodal/tool/thinking payloads\n\nExample backend module:\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.LLMBackend do\n  alias AttractorEx.Outcome\n\n  def run(node, prompt, _context) do\n    # Call your LLM provider here.\n    text = \"Response for #{node.id}: #{prompt}\"\n    Outcome.success(%{\"responses\" => %{node.id => text}}, \"LLM completed\")\n  end\nend\n```\n\nRun with backend:\n\n```elixir\nAttractorEx.run(dot_source, %{}, codergen_backend: MyApp.LLMBackend)\n```\n\nRun with unified client:\n\n```elixir\nllm_client = %AttractorEx.LLM.Client{\n  providers: %{\"openai\" => MyAdapter},\n  default_provider: \"openai\"\n}\n\nAttractorEx.run(dot_source, %{}, llm_client: llm_client)\n```\n\nDefault-client helpers are also available for applications that want a process-wide\nsingleton:\n\n```elixir\nclient = AttractorEx.LLM.Client.from_env()\nAttractorEx.LLM.Client.put_default(client)\n\nresponse =\n  AttractorEx.LLM.Client.generate(%AttractorEx.LLM.Request{\n    model: \"gpt-5.2\",\n    messages: [%AttractorEx.LLM.Message{role: :user, content: \"Plan the change\"}]\n  })\n```\n\nArtifacts written by codergen stage:\n\n1. `prompt.md`\n2. `response.md`\n3. `status.json`\n\n`status.json` follows the Appendix C contract:\n\n1. `outcome`\n2. `preferred_next_label`\n3. `suggested_next_ids`\n4. `context_updates`\n5. `notes`\n\nBackward-compatible aliases such as `status` and `preferred_label` are still emitted.","ref":"readme.html#configuring-llm-nodes-codergen","title":"Configuring LLM Nodes (codergen) - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Coding-agent loop behavior is implemented in the Agent session modules and tracked in:\n\n1. `lib/attractor_ex/CODING_AGENT_LOOP_COMPLIANCE.md`\n2. Source spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/coding-agent-loop-spec.md\n\nUnified LLM behavior is tracked in:\n\n1. `lib/attractor_ex/UNIFIED_LLM_SPEC_COMPLIANCE.md`\n2. Source spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/unified-llm-spec.md\n\nCore Attractor engine behavior is tracked in:\n\n1. `lib/attractor_ex/ATTRACTOR_SPEC_COMPLIANCE.md`\n2. Source spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/attractor-spec.md\n\nThese compliance docs use `implemented` / `partial` / `not implemented` status per upstream section and should be updated whenever upstream spec content changes.\n\nCurrent coding-agent highlights:\n\n1. `ProviderProfile.openai/1`, `ProviderProfile.anthropic/1`, and `ProviderProfile.gemini/1` now expose provider-aligned tool bundles and capability metadata instead of a single shared tool list. OpenAI includes `apply_patch`, Anthropic and Gemini include `edit_file`, and Gemini also includes `read_many_files` plus `list_dir`, with opt-in `web_search`/`web_fetch` support via `ProviderProfile.gemini(web_tools: true)`.\n2. `AttractorEx.Agent.LocalExecutionEnvironment` now exposes file IO, directory listing, globbing, grep, shell execution, and environment metadata through the `ExecutionEnvironment` behaviour.\n3. `AttractorEx.Agent.ApplyPatch` backs the OpenAI-facing `apply_patch` tool for local sessions, handling add/delete/update/move operations in the appendix-style patch envelope.\n4. `AttractorEx.Agent.Session` validates object-style tool arguments, emits spec-style typed session events (including synthesized assistant text deltas and full-output `tool_call_end` host events), layers ancestor project instruction files such as `AGENTS.md`, `CODEX.md`, and `.codex/instructions.md` into the default prompt context under a shared 32 KB budget, and manages spec-style subagent tools (`spawn_agent`, `send_input`, `wait`, `close_agent`) with depth limits.\n5. `AttractorEx.Agent.ProviderProfile` exposes provider-specific base prompt guidance, supports deterministic custom-tool registration/override via `register_tool/2` and `register_tools/2`, and publishes a maintained OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini compatibility matrix covering implemented tool names, reference tool names, capability flags, instruction files, reasoning-option paths, and shared event kinds.","ref":"readme.html#coding-agent-loop-spec-compliance","title":"Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Copy `lib/attractor_ex/` into your project under `lib/`.\n2. Copy `lib/attractor_ex.ex` (public entrypoint module).\n3. Add `{:jason, \"~> 1.2\"}` to dependencies (if not already present).\n4. Copy `test/attractor_ex/` tests (recommended) and run them.\n\nOptional: copy `test/support/attractor_ex_test_*` backend fixtures for spec-style test scenarios.","ref":"readme.html#how-to-extract-into-another-project","title":"How to Extract into Another Project - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"```bash\nmix test test/attractor_ex\nmix coveralls\n```\n\nCoverage is configured to enforce a 90% minimum for AttractorEx scope.","ref":"readme.html#verification-commands","title":"Verification Commands - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. https://github.com/strongdm/attractor\n2. https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/attractor-spec.md\n3. https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/coding-agent-loop-spec.md\n4. https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/unified-llm-spec.md\n5. Local compliance docs:\n   - `lib/attractor_ex/ATTRACTOR_SPEC_COMPLIANCE.md`\n   - `lib/attractor_ex/CODING_AGENT_LOOP_COMPLIANCE.md`\n   - `lib/attractor_ex/UNIFIED_LLM_SPEC_COMPLIANCE.md`\n6. Baseline commit currently implemented/tested against:\n   `2f892efd63ee7c11f038856b90aae57c067b77c2` (verified 2026-03-06)","ref":"readme.html#spec-reference","title":"Spec Reference - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Refresh local reference clone: `git -C ..\\\\_attractor_reference fetch --all --prune`\n2. Compare baseline: `git -C ..\\\\_attractor_reference rev-parse HEAD`\n3. If changed, review spec diff and update `AttractorEx` tests first, then implementation.","ref":"readme.html#keeping-up-with-upstream","title":"Keeping Up with Upstream - AttractorEx (Standalone Library)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)\n\nThis document tracks current compliance against the upstream Attractor specification and is written to render cleanly in ExDoc.","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html","title":"Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- Attractor spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/attractor-spec.md\n- Repository: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor\n- Upstream HEAD reviewed: `2f892efd63ee7c11f038856b90aae57c067b77c2` (checked 2026-03-06)","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#source-documents","title":"Source Documents - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#scope","title":"Scope - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. `lib/attractor_ex/parser.ex`\n2. `lib/attractor_ex/validator.ex`\n3. `lib/attractor_ex/engine.ex`\n4. `lib/attractor_ex/condition.ex`\n5. `lib/attractor_ex/handlers/*.ex`","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#primary-implementation","title":"Primary Implementation - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. `test/attractor_ex/dot_schema_test.exs`\n2. `test/attractor_ex/parser_test.exs`\n3. `test/attractor_ex/validator_test.exs`\n4. `test/attractor_ex/condition_test.exs`\n5. `test/attractor_ex/handlers_test.exs`\n6. `test/attractor_ex/engine_test.exs`","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#primary-tests","title":"Primary Tests - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Legend: `implemented`, `partial`, `not implemented`.\n\n| Upstream section | Status |\n| --- | --- |\n| `2. DOT DSL Schema` | `partial` |\n| `3. Pipeline Execution Engine` | `implemented` |\n| `4. Node Handlers` | `implemented` |\n| `5. State and Context` | `implemented` |\n| `6. Human-in-the-Loop` | `implemented` |\n| `7. Validation and Linting` | `implemented` |\n| `8. Model Stylesheet` | `implemented` |\n| `9. Transforms and Extensibility` | `implemented` |\n| `10. Condition Expression Language` | `implemented` |\n| `11. Definition of Done` | `implemented` |\n| `Appendix A/B/C/D` | `partial` |","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#status-summary","title":"Status Summary - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"### `2. DOT DSL Schema` — `partial`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- Directed graphs, chained edges, and order-sensitive node and edge defaults\n- `strict digraph`\n- Compact attr statements such as `graph[...]`, `node[...]`, and `edge[...]`\n- Multi-line, repeated, comma-separated, and semicolon-separated attr blocks\n- Class attrs and shape mapping\n- Bare, quoted, and HTML-like graph and node identifiers\n- Bare graph IDs with hyphens and numeric node IDs\n- Single-quoted and double-quoted attr values\n- Escaped newline, tab, and carriage-return handling in quoted strings\n- Quote-aware statement splitting and comment stripping\n- Node-port edge endpoint parsing such as `a:out -> b:in:nw`\n- Recursive inline and nested `subgraph` flattening\n- Scoped default inheritance and subgraph-label-derived classes\n- Subgraphs used directly as edge endpoints\n\nNot yet complete:\n\n- Full Graphviz grammar parity\n\n### `3. Pipeline Execution Engine` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- Start-to-exit execution loop\n- Edge selection priority\n- Goal gates\n- Retries and backoff\n- Failure routing\n- Loop restart handling\n- Checkpoint, manifest, and status artifacts\n- Spec default `default_max_retry=50` behavior\n\n### `4. Node Handlers` — `implemented`\n\nBuilt-in handlers present:\n\n- `start`\n- `exit`\n- `codergen`\n- `wait.human`\n- `conditional`\n- `parallel`\n- `parallel.fan_in`\n- `tool`\n- `stack.manager_loop`\n- default fallback\n\n### `5. State and Context` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- Context merge behavior\n- `graph.*` context mirroring\n- `current_node` tracking\n- Per-node artifacts and checkpoints\n- First-class resume API via `AttractorEx.resume/3`\n- Resume from checkpoint struct, map, or `checkpoint.json`\n\n### `6. Human-in-the-Loop` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- Context-driven answers\n- Timeout and default handling\n- Blank-answer default routing\n- Unmatched-answer fallback to the first outgoing choice\n- Skip handling\n- Single-select and multi-select routing via `human.multiple`\n- Structured answer normalization\n- Interviewer abstractions: `AutoApprove`, `Console`, `Callback`, `Queue`, `Recording`, `Server`\n- Optional `ask_multiple/4` and `inform/4` interviewer callbacks\n- Shared normalized question contract:\n  - `FREEFORM`\n  - `CONFIRMATION`\n  - `YES_NO`\n  - `MULTIPLE_CHOICE`\n- Rich structured answer extraction:\n  - `answer`\n  - `value`\n  - `selected`\n  - `answers`\n  - `keys`\n- Console prompt/default/timeout/input-mode metadata\n- JSON-structured console input\n- Recording interviewer answer payload capture\n- Server interviewer pending-question exposure\n- Server-side choice metadata:\n  - `multiple`\n  - `required`\n  - input mode\n  - choice count\n- `human.required` and `human.input` metadata overrides\n- Immediate pending-question registration before `InterviewStarted`\n- Answer payload metadata on completion events\n- Day-based timeout suffix parsing such as `1d`\n\n### `7. Validation and Linting` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- `Validator.validate/2`\n- `Validator.validate_or_raise/2`\n- Start and exit structure checks\n- Edge source and target existence checks\n- Condition parse errors\n- Reachability errors and dead-end flow warnings\n- Retry-target reference checks\n- Graph-level `retry_target` and `fallback_retry_target`\n- Spec-aligned `retry_target_exists` lint metadata\n- Graph-level retry-path reachability\n- Retry-count linting for `default_max_retry` and node `max_retries`\n- Goal-gate retry hints without false positives when graph-level retry targets exist\n- Prompt-or-label warnings for nodes that resolve to the codergen handler\n- Unknown explicit node types\n- Fidelity value linting\n- Stylesheet syntax errors\n- `wait.human` choice and default checks\n- Prompt-presence lint\n- Ambiguous default-choice lint\n- `human.multiple`, `human.required`, and `human.input` attr linting\n- Timeout/default lint when `human.timeout` lacks `human.default_choice`\n- Timeout-format linting\n- Duplicate human accelerator key warnings\n- Codergen LLM attr linting:\n  - `reasoning_effort`\n  - `temperature`\n  - `max_tokens`\n  - provider/model pairing\n- `parallel` attr linting:\n  - `join_policy`\n  - `max_parallel`\n  - `k`\n  - `quorum_ratio`\n- `stack.manager_loop` attr linting:\n  - `manager.actions`\n  - `manager.max_cycles`\n  - `manager.poll_interval`\n  - `stack.child_autostart`\n  - autostart `stack.child_dotfile`\n- `allow_partial` boolean linting\n- Stylesheet lint diagnostics\n- Spec-aligned `rule` metadata on diagnostics\n- Custom lint rule hooks through `validate/2`\n- Error escalation through `validate_or_raise/2`\n\nCoverage basis:\n\n- Primary: `validator_test.exs`\n- Public API wrappers: `attractor_ex_test.exs`\n\n### `8. Model Stylesheet` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- CSS-like `model_stylesheet` parsing\n- Selectors:\n  - `*`\n  - shape selectors such as `box`\n  - `.class`\n  - `#id`\n  - `type=...`\n  - `node[type=...]`\n  - `shape=...`\n  - `node[shape=...]`\n  - compound selectors\n  - selector lists\n  - dotted handler types such as `wait.human`\n  - single-quoted selector values such as `node[type='wait.human']`\n- Specificity ordering and same-specificity last-rule wins behavior\n- Pre-validation application while preserving explicit node attrs as the final override\n- Backward-compatible JSON stylesheet parsing\n- CSS declaration support for:\n  - codergen LLM attrs\n  - operational attrs such as `timeout`, `prompt`, `command`, and retry attrs\n  - `human.*` attrs including `human.multiple`, `human.required`, and `human.input`\n- Both `:` and `=` declaration separators\n- `model` -> `llm_model` aliasing\n- Quoted values with escapes\n- CSS comments\n- Quoted `/* ... */` comment markers\n- Quoted `;` and `}` characters inside declaration values\n- Invalid selectors ignored during parse so lint can report them non-fatally\n\nLint diagnostics cover:\n\n- Unknown CSS properties\n- Malformed declarations\n- Invalid selectors\n- Invalid CSS syntax\n- Invalid JSON list or map rule shapes\n\n### `9. Transforms and Extensibility` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- Extensibility via handlers, backends, and runtime options\n- Graph transform pipeline through:\n  - `graph_transforms`\n  - legacy `graph_transform`\n- Function hooks plus module transforms supporting:\n  - spec-style `apply/1`\n  - backward-compatible `transform/1`\n- Built-in transforms:\n  - stylesheet application\n  - `$goal` variable expansion\n  - runtime preamble synthesis for non-`full` codergen stages\n- Optional HTTP server mode through `AttractorEx.start_http_server/1`\n- Section-9 core HTTP endpoint set:\n  - pipeline status\n  - SSE events\n  - cancellation\n  - question and answer\n  - checkpoint\n  - context\n  - graph responses in SVG, DOT, JSON, Mermaid, and plain text\n- Definition-of-done compatibility aliases:\n  - `POST /run`\n  - `GET /status`\n  - `POST /answer`\n- HTTP hardening:\n  - empty pipeline submissions rejected\n  - unsupported graph formats rejected with explicit `400`\n  - oversized request bodies rejected with explicit `413`\n  - `no-store` and `nosniff` response headers\n  - 1 MB JSON body limit by default\n\n### `10. Condition Expression Language` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented and tested:\n\n- Equality and inequality\n- Numeric comparisons\n- Clause chaining\n- Nil and boolean handling\n- Nested context and `outcome` access\n\n### `11. Definition of Done` — `implemented`\n\nImplemented:\n\n- Definition-of-done coverage across parser, validator, engine, handlers, interviewer flows, stylesheet support, transforms, and HTTP tests\n- Section `11.11` HTTP compatibility aliases:\n  - `POST /run`\n  - `GET /status`\n  - `POST /answer`\n\n### `Appendix A/B/C/D` — `partial`\n\nRepresented today:\n\n- Major attrs\n- Shape mapping\n- Status contract\n- Error categories\n- Graph-level `tool_hooks.pre` and `tool_hooks.post`\n- `stack.child_workdir`\n- Appendix C `status.json` fields:\n  - `outcome`\n  - `preferred_next_label`\n  - `suggested_next_ids`\n  - `context_updates`\n  - `notes`\n- Backward-compatible status aliases\n- Appendix D-style runtime error categorization surfaced on outcomes, terminal results, and failure events\n\nNot yet complete:\n\n- Full appendix coverage","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#section-details","title":"Section Details - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. DOT parsing and schema: `dot_schema_test.exs` and `parser_test.exs`\n   Evidence includes `strict digraph`, compact attr statements, quoted and HTML-like graph/node identifiers, bare graph IDs with hyphens, numeric node IDs, repeated attr blocks, line-, comma-, and semicolon-separated attr declarations, escaped newline and tab handling, node-port endpoint parsing, and subgraph edge endpoint expansion.\n2. Validation diagnostics: `validator_test.exs` plus public wrapper coverage in `attractor_ex_test.exs`\n   Evidence includes start/exit structure, reachability including graph-level retry paths, condition syntax metadata, retry-target and retry-count linting, goal-gate retry hints, `wait.human` prompt/default/timeout checks, codergen/parallel/manager attr linting, stylesheet diagnostics, custom rules, diagnostic `rule` metadata, and `validate_or_raise/2`.\n3. Engine routing, retries, and goal gates: `engine_test.exs`\n4. Condition language semantics: `condition_test.exs`\n5. Built-in handlers: `handlers_test.exs`\n6. Graph transform pipeline, spec-style `apply/1` compatibility, built-in variable expansion, runtime preamble synthesis, and transform error handling: `engine_test.exs`\n7. CSS and JSON stylesheet parsing plus parser handling of quoted separators, escaped strings, quoted comment markers, CSS comments, shape selectors, `model=` aliasing, single-quoted selector values, dotted handler-type selectors, operational CSS attrs, and invalid selector diagnostics: `model_stylesheet_test.exs` and `parser_test.exs`\n8. Human interviewer adapters, recording wrapper, optional multi-select/inform callbacks, end-to-end `wait.human` multi-select routing, console prompt metadata, first-choice fallback, and server-side question inference and metadata: `handlers_test.exs`, `interviewers_test.exs`, and `interviewer_server_test.exs`\n9. HTTP server mode, SSE events, pending question flow, answer submission, SVG/DOT/JSON/Mermaid/plain-text graph variants, compatibility aliases, invalid-request handling, and pending-question metadata exposure: `http_test.exs`","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#evidence-highlights","title":"Evidence Highlights - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Full Graphviz DOT grammar parity remains incomplete beyond the supported runtime-oriented subset.\n2. Examples of missing DOT parity include richer HTML-string fidelity, richer endpoint forms, and unsupported `attr_stmt` variations that do not map cleanly to AttractorEx execution semantics.","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#known-gaps-vs-spec","title":"Known Gaps vs Spec - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"```bash\nmix test test/attractor_ex/dot_schema_test.exs\nmix test test/attractor_ex/parser_test.exs test/attractor_ex/validator_test.exs\nmix test test/attractor_ex/condition_test.exs test/attractor_ex/handlers_test.exs test/attractor_ex/engine_test.exs\nmix test test/attractor_ex/interviewer_server_test.exs\nmix test test/attractor_ex/http_test.exs\nmix docs\nmix precommit\n```","ref":"attractor_spec_compliance.html#verification-commands","title":"Verification Commands - Attractor Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)\n\nThis file maps `AttractorEx.Agent.*` behavior to the upstream coding-agent-loop specification.","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html","title":"Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- Coding-agent loop spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/coding-agent-loop-spec.md\n- Related unified LLM spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/unified-llm-spec.md\n- Upstream HEAD reviewed: `2f892efd63ee7c11f038856b90aae57c067b77c2` (checked 2026-03-06)","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html#source-documents","title":"Source Documents - Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Implementation:\n\n1. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/session.ex`\n2. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/session_config.ex`\n3. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/provider_profile.ex`\n4. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/builtin_tools.ex`\n5. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/apply_patch.ex`\n6. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/tool.ex`\n7. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/tool_registry.ex`\n8. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/execution_environment.ex`\n9. `lib/attractor_ex/agent/local_execution_environment.ex`\n\nTests:\n\n1. `test/attractor_ex/agent/session_test.exs`\n2. `test/attractor_ex/agent/primitives_test.exs`\n3. `test/attractor_ex/agent/builtin_tools_test.exs`","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html#scope","title":"Scope - Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Legend: `implemented`, `partial`, `not implemented`.\n\n| Upstream section | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `2. Agentic Loop` | `implemented` | Session lifecycle, loop rounds, natural completion, limits, steering/follow-up, loop detection, spec-style session event emission, full-output tool-call host events, and model-recoverable tool validation failures are covered. |\n| `3. Provider-Aligned Toolsets` | `implemented` | OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini presets now expose provider-specific tool bundles and capability flags, including OpenAI `apply_patch`, Anthropic/Gemini `edit_file`, Gemini `read_many_files`/`list_dir`, provider-native `shell` naming, and opt-in Gemini `web_search`/`web_fetch` support via `ProviderProfile.gemini(web_tools: true)`. Byte-for-byte upstream harness/prompt parity is still not claimed. |\n| `4. Tool Execution Environment` | `implemented` | `ExecutionEnvironment` now covers working directory, platform, file reads/writes, directory listing, globbing, grep, shell execution, and environment context, with `LocalExecutionEnvironment` implementing the contract. |\n| `5. Tool Output and Context Management` | `implemented` | Character-first then line truncation, per-tool limits, timeout controls, and bounded event payload behavior are implemented/tested. |\n| `6. System Prompts and Environment Context` | `implemented` | Layered prompt construction now includes provider-specific base guidance, provider/model metadata, platform, tool inventory, serialized environment context, and ancestor-discovered instruction docs (`AGENTS.md`, provider files, `.codex/instructions.md`) with root-to-leaf ordering, a shared 32 KB budget, and custom builder hooks preserved. |\n| `7. Subagents` | `implemented` | Session-managed `spawn_agent`, `send_input`, `wait`, and `close_agent` tools now create child sessions with independent history, shared execution environment, model/turn overrides, and enforced `max_subagent_depth`. |\n| `8. Out of Scope` | `n/a` | Informational section. |\n| `9. Definition of Done` | `implemented` | The session loop, provider presets, registry dispatch/error paths, truncation policy, steering/follow-up controls, reasoning controls, layered prompt context, local execution environment contract, subagent lifecycle, and maintained event surface are implemented and covered by tests. Exact provider-native prompt/tool-harness parity is still tracked separately as a known non-blocking gap. |\n| `Appendix A (apply_patch v4a)` | `partial` | A built-in `apply_patch` tool now parses and applies add/delete/update/move operations in the appendix-style envelope for local sessions. Full appendix-edge-case coverage and exhaustive parity validation remain open. |\n| `Appendix B (error handling)` | `partial` | Tool/session error propagation and recovery behaviors are implemented, but full cross-provider SDK retry hierarchy is delegated to Unified LLM layer. |","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html#section-by-section-status","title":"Section-by-Section Status - Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Session lifecycle and closure/abort behavior.\n2. Tool call normalization and robust argument parsing.\n3. Unknown tool error results (model-recoverable).\n4. Steering and follow-up sequencing.\n5. Loop detection and turn/tool-round limits.\n6. Parallel tool call execution when enabled by profile.\n7. Timeout handling including late message drainage.\n8. Character+line truncation behavior and bounded event output.\n9. Tool failure capture (`raise`/`throw`/`exit`) and LLM error shutdown.\n10. Spec-aligned session event surface including `assistant_text_start`, `assistant_text_delta`, `tool_call_output_delta`, `error`, and full untruncated `tool_call_end` payloads for host integrations.\n11. Reasoning effort default/override and working-dir fallback logic.\n12. Provider presets with provider-specific coding-agent tool bundles, capability flags, and a maintained OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini integration matrix.\n13. Execution-environment file/glob/grep/shell primitives.\n14. Tool-argument schema validation and session/context warning events.\n15. Root-to-leaf ancestor-based project instruction discovery for prompt context with a shared 32 KB truncation budget.\n16. Subagent lifecycle including spawn/input/wait/close flows, depth enforcement, and recoverable missing-agent errors.\n17. OpenAI-style `apply_patch` execution for local sessions plus Anthropic/Gemini-native edit/read-many/list-dir tool variants and opt-in Gemini `web_search`/`web_fetch`.\n18. Deterministic custom-tool registration on top of provider presets, including name-collision override behavior.\n19. Provider-specific base system-prompt guidance and the full typed session event inventory exposed via `Event.supported_kinds/0`.","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html#verified-behaviors-with-tests","title":"Verified Behaviors (with tests) - Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Provider-packaged toolsets and prompt bodies are aligned to codex-rs, Claude Code, and gemini-cli behaviors, but are not yet byte-for-byte harness copies.\n2. Built-in Gemini web tools are opt-in rather than enabled in the default preset to preserve a conservative local/network posture.\n3. `apply_patch` coverage is intentionally conservative and not yet validated against every appendix edge case.","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html#known-gaps-vs-spec","title":"Known Gaps vs Spec - Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"```bash\nmix test test/attractor_ex/agent/primitives_test.exs test/attractor_ex/agent/session_test.exs\nmix docs\nmix precommit\n```","ref":"coding_agent_loop_compliance.html#verification-commands","title":"Verification Commands - Coding Agent Loop Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"# Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)\n\nThis file tracks compliance of `AttractorEx.LLM.*` with the upstream unified LLM client specification.","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html","title":"Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"- Unified LLM spec: https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/unified-llm-spec.md\n- Coding-agent loop spec (consumer of this layer): https://github.com/strongdm/attractor/blob/main/coding-agent-loop-spec.md\n- Upstream HEAD reviewed: `2f892efd63ee7c11f038856b90aae57c067b77c2` (checked 2026-03-06)","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html#source-documents","title":"Source Documents - Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Implementation:\n\n1. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/client.ex`\n2. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/request.ex`\n3. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/response.ex`\n4. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/message.ex`\n5. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/usage.ex`\n6. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/stream_event.ex`\n7. `lib/attractor_ex/llm/provider_adapter.ex`\n\nTests and fixtures:\n\n1. `test/attractor_ex/llm_client_test.exs`\n2. `test/support/attractor_ex_test_llm_adapter.ex`\n3. `test/support/attractor_ex_test_llm_error_adapter.ex`\n4. `test/support/attractor_ex_test_unified_llm_adapter.ex`","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html#scope","title":"Scope - Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"Legend: `implemented`, `partial`, `not implemented`.\n\n| Upstream section | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `2. Architecture` | `partial` | Programmatic client config, provider resolution, middleware chain, adapter boundary, env-based construction (`from_env/1`), and module-level default client helpers are implemented. Model catalog and prompt caching machinery are still open. |\n| `3. Data Model` | `partial` | Core request/response/usage/stream event/message structs exist. Messages now support tagged `MessagePart` content blocks, but full provider-round-trip multimodal semantics are still incomplete. |\n| `4. Generation and Streaming` | `partial` | Low-level `complete`/raw `stream` plus `complete_with_request` and `stream_with_request` are implemented. High-level `generate`, stream accumulation, `generate_object`, and `stream_object` helpers are now implemented. Incremental typed object streaming is still not implemented. |\n| `5. Tool Calling` | `partial` | Request/response fields support tool call payload transfer. Automatic high-level multi-step tool loop at this SDK layer is not implemented here (handled in agent session layer). |\n| `6. Error Handling and Retry` | `not implemented` | Typed error hierarchy, retry taxonomy, backoff/retry-after handling are not implemented in this layer. |\n| `7. Provider Adapter Contract` | `partial` | Adapter behavior contract (`complete`, optional `stream`) and unsupported-stream handling exist. Full provider translation guidance and concrete provider implementations are not included. |\n| `8. Definition of Done` | `partial` | Core routing/middleware coverage exists and now includes env/default-client construction, message-part projection, stream accumulation, and JSON object helpers. Provider-native adapters, full multimodal round-trip parity, retries, and caching parity remain open. |","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html#section-by-section-status","title":"Section-by-Section Status - Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Provider routing by explicit/default provider.\n2. Errors for missing/unregistered providers.\n3. Middleware request transformation for complete and stream.\n4. `complete_with_request/2` and `stream_with_request/2` return resolved requests.\n5. Stream adapter dispatch and unsupported-stream error path.\n6. Request field pass-through including reasoning/cache usage counters.\n7. `from_env/1` runtime construction and module-level default client helpers.\n8. Message-part content projection for richer request payloads.\n9. Stream accumulation into a normalized final response.\n10. JSON object decoding for non-streaming and streaming helper APIs.","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html#verified-behaviors-with-tests","title":"Verified Behaviors (with tests) - Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"1. Full content-part round-trip semantics across concrete provider adapters remain incomplete even though the normalized message model now supports tagged parts.\n2. Incremental typed object streaming is not implemented; `stream_object/2` currently accumulates the underlying event stream before decoding.\n3. Built-in tool-loop orchestration at unified client layer.\n4. Error taxonomy and automatic retries with jitter/retry-after.\n5. Native provider adapters for OpenAI Responses, Anthropic Messages, Gemini APIs.\n6. Prompt caching provider-specific behaviors.","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html#known-gaps-vs-spec","title":"Known Gaps vs Spec - Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"},{"doc":"```bash\nmix test test/attractor_ex/llm_client_test.exs\nmix precommit\n```","ref":"unified_llm_spec_compliance.html#verification-commands","title":"Verification Commands - Unified LLM Spec Compliance (AttractorEx)","type":"extras"}],"producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"},"proglang":"elixir"}